# Android → HarmonyOS Migration Rules

You are converting Android code to idiomatic HarmonyOS. Follow these rules.

## Language: Kotlin/Java → ArkTS
- `val`→`const`, `var`→`let` with type annotations
- `String?`→`string | null`, `?:`→`??`, `?.`→`?.`
- `data class`→`@Observed class` with constructor
- `suspend fun`→`async` returning `Promise<T>`
- `sealed class`→discriminated union (`type` field)
- No `any` type, no extension functions, no structural typing for classes

## UI: Compose/XML → ArkUI
- `@Composable fun`→`@Component struct` with `build()` method
- `remember { mutableStateOf() }`→`@State` decorator
- Params→`@Prop` (one-way) or `@Link` (two-way)
- Modifier chain→method chaining AFTER build block: `Column() { }.width('100%')`
- `LazyColumn { items() }`→`List() { ForEach(data, builder, keyGen) }` — key generator required
- `Button(onClick){Text()}`→`Button('label').onClick()`
- Navigation targets need `@Entry` + `main_pages.json` registration

## APIs
- SharedPreferences→`preferences` from `@kit.ArkData` (async)
- Room→`relationalStore` from `@kit.ArkData`
- Retrofit/OkHttp→`http` from `@kit.NetworkKit` (destroy in finally)
- NavController→`router` from `@kit.ArkUI`
- `R.drawable.x`→`$r('app.media.x')`, `R.string.x`→`$r('app.string.x')`
- Context→`common.UIAbilityContext` from `@kit.AbilityKit`

## Architecture
- Activity→UIAbility, Fragment→@Component struct
- ViewModel→`@Observed` class, LiveData→`@State`
- Hilt/Dagger→manual DI, Application→AbilityStage

## Critical
- Methods AFTER build block: `Column(){...}.width('100%')` ✅
- ForEach needs key generator (3rd arg) ✅
- No `any` type ✅
- Destroy HTTP requests in `finally` ✅
- No sync I/O in `build()` ✅
- `@State` only tracks first-level — use `@Observed`+`@ObjectLink` for nested ✅
